  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Source</strong> <em>Ranged Tactics Toolbox pg. 0</em>, <em>Adventurer's Armory pg. 4</em>, <em>Advanced Player's Guide pg. 179</em>, <em>Ultimate Equipment pg. 19</em></p><h3><span title=\"PFS Legal\">[PFS]</span> Statistics</h3><p><strong>Cost</strong> 5 gp <strong>Weight</strong> 4 lbs.</p><p><strong>Damage</strong> 1d6 (small), 1d8 (medium); <strong>Critical</strong> x2; <strong>Range</strong> 20 ft.; <strong>Type</strong> P; <strong>Special</strong> see text</p><p><strong>Category</strong> Ranged; <strong>Proficiency</strong> Martial</p><p><strong>Weapon Groups</strong> Spears; Thrown</p><h3>Description</h3><p>The tip of this heavy javelin is designed to break off and embed itself into a shield once it hits. Like ammunition, a thrown pilum that hits its target is destroyed. If you hit a shieldbearing opponent with a pilum, he loses the AC bonuses from that shield until he takes a standard action to pry the remnants of the pilum from his shield.</p>"
